
Add three groups to Machine named India, Australia & Japan. Add three primary users to the group India named Delhi, Mumbai & kolkata. Delhi user can access the documents of mumbai user in read only mode whereas mumbai can access the documents of delhi user with full access. Mumbai is secondary member of Australia Group and his default home directory is /home/bombay. Mumbai & Delhi both users can access the documents of kolkata user in read only mode, whole world can access the documents of kolkata user with full permission. Add two users to group Australia named sydney and melbourne. Melbourne user does not have interactive shell in machine. sydney user is primary group member of australia group and can access the document of mumbai user in read only mode and his default UID is 3001. All passwords are redhat
